<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>MediaLab Terms of Service</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.png" type="image/png" />
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
      <a href="/" class="text-cyan-300 text-sm font-bold">Back to MediaLab</a>
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">Terms of Service</h1>
      <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-slate-300 leading-7">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Use of the platform</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">MediaLab is provided for lawful creative, publishing, and productivity workflows. You must not use the platform to publish malicious, fraudulent, infringing, or abusive content.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Accounts and integrations</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">You are responsible for the accounts you connect, the content you publish, and the payout details you submit. MediaLab may suspend access where misuse, fraud, or platform abuse is detected.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Payouts and monetization</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">Withdrawal requests are reviewed and may be delayed, denied, or reversed where there are accuracy, compliance, or fraud concerns. Connected monetization services remain subject to their own approval policies.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Service availability</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">We aim for a reliable service, but MediaLab is provided on an as-available basis. External providers such as GitHub Pages, Google, and Render can affect publishing, hosting, and reporting behavior.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
